<div class="header">
    <div class="icon"></div>
    <h2>Employees</h2>
    <span class="hint">Number of full-time equivalent employees</span>
    <input type="text" class="valueBox" />
    <span class="prompt">Please enter <br />how many employees you have</span>
    <div class="gauge "></div>
    <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="button medium runReport ">Run Report</a>
    <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="reportToggle"></a>
</div>
<div class="body ">
    <div class="loading">
        <p class="title">Employee Report</p>
        <img src="@Url.Content("~/content/images/Loading.gif")?@SizeUp.Core.Web.CacheBuster.Buster" alt="Loading" />
        <p class="message">Generating Report</p>
    </div>
    <div class="reportContainer ">
        <div class="reportContent noDataError hidden">
            <p>No data available to display this report</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reportContent averageEmployees reportData">
            <h3>How you size up</h3>
            <p class="description">
                <div data-template="averageEmployeesDescription">
                @Html.Raw(ViewBag.Strings["Dashboard.AverageEmployees.Description"])
                </div>
            </p>
            <div class="chart">
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="mapToggle" data-toggleText="View Variations by Geography">Hide Variations by Geography</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="chartToggle" data-toggleText="View Chart">View Data Table</a>
                <div class="container"></div>
            </div>
            <table class="table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="label">Business/Geography</td>
                        <td class="value">Value</td>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="container">
                    <tr data-template="AverageEmployeesTableRow">
                        <td class="name">{{name}}</td>
                        <td class="value">{{value}}</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            <ul class="links">
                <li>
                    <a class="source button inverse" href="javascript:void(0);" data-toggleText="Hide">Source</a>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <div class="sourceContent " data-expandedClass="expanded">
                @Html.Raw(ViewBag.Strings["Dashboard.AverageEmployees.Source"])
            </div>
            <div class="mapWrapper container">
                <div data-template="legendTitle" class="legend titleWrap">
                    <p class="backdrop edge title"><span class="text"></span></p>
                </div>
                <div data-template="legendContainer" class="legend backdrop edge">
                    <ul class="legend legendContainer">
                        <li data-template="legendItem"><div class="block" data-override-style="background-color: {{color}};"></div><span class="range text">{{label}}</span></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="map"></div>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="textAlternative">Text Alternative</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="reportSidebar  averageEmployees reportData">
            <div class="section considerations collapsable">
                @Html.Raw(ViewBag.Strings["Dashboard.AverageEmployees.Considerations"])
                <div class="question">
                    <span>Are you a relatively <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="large">large</a> or <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="small">small</a> business?</span>
                </div>
                <div class="large answer collapsed hidden">
                    <h5>you are a large business</h5>
                    <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="clearer">[change]</a>
                    <p>
                        Being large is often a sign of success and stability, showing that your particular
                         business model is a good one.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        A large business typically has access to more resources which can be used to invest
                         in the future of the company in areas outside of the company's basic operations 
                        (e.g., research and development, new products, advertising).
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Large businesses often have economies of scale that can allow for higher profits and
                         pass-through savings to customers.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="small answer collapsed hidden">
                    <h5>you are a small business</h5>
                    <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="clearer">[change]</a>
                    <p>
                        Small businesses can gain advantages by being more nimble than their larger 
                        competition and responding rapidly to changing conditions. They should be ready
                         to shift direction to take advantage of new opportunities in the marketplace,
                         or restructure during hard times.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Small businesses should have fewer administrative needs due to their smaller size,
                         which saves costs.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Small businesses can succeed by focusing on developing more personal relationships
                         with their customers. Customers can more easily get to know the few people in a small
                         business.
                    </p>
                </div>


            </div>
            <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="considerationToggle fadeToggle" data-toggleText="More" data-toggleClass="collapsed">Less</a>
            <div class="section resources collapsable">
                @Html.Raw(ViewBag.Strings["Dashboard.AverageEmployees.Resources"])
                <p class="notice"><a href="/help/contact">Get listed as a resource</a></p>
            </div>
            <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="resourcesToggle fadeToggle" data-toggleText="More" data-toggleClass="collapsed">Less</a>
        </div>





        <div class="reportContent employeesPerCapita reportData">
            <h3>How your community sizes up</h3>
            <p class="description">
                <div data-template="employeesPerCapitaDescription">
                @Html.Raw(ViewBag.Strings["Dashboard.EmployeesPerCapita.Description"])
                </div>
            </p>
            <div class="chart">
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="mapToggle" data-toggleText="View Variations by Geography">Hide Variations by Geography</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="chartToggle" data-toggleText="View Chart">View Data Table</a>
                <div class="container"></div>
            </div>
            <table class="table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="label">Business/Geography</td>
                        <td class="value">Value</td>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="container">
                    <tr data-template="employeesPerCapitaTableRow">
                        <td class="name">{{name}}</td>
                        <td class="value">{{value}}</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            <ul class="links">
                <li>
                    <a class="source button inverse" href="javascript:void(0);" data-toggleText="Hide">Source</a>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <div class="sourceContent " data-expandedClass="expanded">
                @Html.Raw(ViewBag.Strings["Dashboard.EmployeesPerCapita.Source"])
            </div>
            <div class="mapWrapper container">
                <div data-template="legendTitle" class="legend titleWrap">
                    <p class="backdrop edge title"><span class="text"></span></p>
                </div>
                <div data-template="legendContainer" class="legend backdrop edge">
                    <ul class="legend legendContainer">
                        <li data-template="legendItem"><div class="block" data-override-style="background-color: {{color}};"></div><span class="range text">{{label}}</span></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="map"></div>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="textAlternative">Text Alternative</a>
            </div>
        </div>
         <div class="reportSidebar  employeesPerCapita reportData">
            <div class="section considerations collapsable">
                @Html.Raw(ViewBag.Strings["Dashboard.EmployeesPerCapita.Considerations"])
            </div>
            <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="considerationToggle fadeToggle" data-toggleText="More" data-toggleClass="collapsed">Less</a>
        </div>




    </div>
</div>